Definition: a hostile meeting of opposing military forces in the course of a war
Example: Grant won a decisive victory in the battle of Chickamauga; he lost his romantic ideas about war when he got into a real engagement
Synonyms: verb, competition, conflict, fight, engagement, social, engage, military_action, war, p, noun, group, military, c, a, hostile, meeting, of, opposing, forces, in, the, course, Grant, won, decisive, victory, Chickamauga, he, lost, his, romantic, ideas, about, when, got, into, real
Category: noun.act
